instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle follows the MBSE abstraction hierarchy defined in the document: (1) Requirements – captured with SysML requirement diagrams; (2) Functional Architecture – represented through SysML block definition diagrams and interface specifications, or ADLs such as ACME or AADL; (3) Logical Architecture – modeled with MontiArc automaton extensions and SysML sequence/activity diagrams; (4) Product/Technical Layer – realized by simulation models in MathWorks Simulink or generated C++/Java code. Transition management between these phases relies on traceability links between the different modeling notations and a version‑controlled model repository (e.g., Git). Governance of the lifecycle is supported by the RFLP methodology (Requirements, Functions, Logics, Physics) and the SMArDT approach to refine twin representations progressively from abstract concepts to concrete product models."
]
